Creating Django Application And Configuring To Run With Gunicorn

#Creating a django application: 
django-admin startproject <app_name> 

#Traverse into the app root folder and perform db migrations using below couple of commands 
python manage.py makemigrations 
python manage.py migrate 

#Creating superuser by executing the below command and follow instructions 
python manage.py createsuperuser  

#Running django application: 
python manage.py runserver 127.0.0.1:8000 

#Open browser and check out http://127.0.0.1:8000 which shows that the app is up and running.


#Installing Gunicorn: 
pip install gunicorn 

#activate the virtual environment in which gunicorn installed and check whether we are able to run the app using it. 
#navigate to the app root dirrectory.access django app at 127.0.0.1:8000 

#Running django app at 127.0.0.1:8000 
gunicorn <app_name>.wsgi:application --bind 127.0.0.1:8000 
